text: hi everyone anthony fantano here
internet's busiest music nerd going to
do a quick
simple
straightforward review of the new
glasser album interiors glasser is the
musical project of producer singer
songwriter cameron micero this is her
second full-length album her full-length
debut ring kind of a short lp but still
one of my favorites of that year brought
together elements of electronic
production
and midi and her really beautiful
soaring vocals and uh the the the style
of
just music underneath her vocals was
really synthetic but also very primal
very i don't want to say basic or
simple but it was kind of this
rudimentary old world feel to the
grooves and just the pacing and the and
the growth and the progression of the
tracks that was kind of seductive
beautiful
hypnotizing and something that just uh
felt archaic in kind of a way now this
lp did earn
cameron some bjork comparisons all
around from
numerous music fans and and critics as
well
and while there was a really obvious
influence there coming from the world of
bjork uh it didn't really get me down
because i thought the songs were so
catchy the melodies were so good and i
thought this very rootsy primal feel to
some of the beats and the progressions
of the songs had glasser kind of in its
own little camp you know like oh this is
obviously an influence but this is her
style this is something that she
approaches songs with this is something
that if i heard it in one of her songs
i'd be like oh well this is definitely a
glasser song so i wasn't really down
with the whole like makeup york
comparison but sort of in a negative
light kind of thing because i was
appreciating what glasser was doing as a
project on its own and i wasn't even
hoping i was just assuming it was a sure
thing that on glasser's next full-length
lp not only would her influences
diversify a little bit in her music at
least because i know she's into artists
like lori anderson who who i also have a
great love for her work but i just
expected this sophomore full-length lp
to be a bit more
original and honestly i can't even say
that it is as original as glasser's
debut in fact i feel like there is an
increased production value on this album
which is good and i think the
compositions and the atmosphere are a
little more vast but i feel like glasser
has taken all of this extra all of this
new effort and
merely put it toward
i don't even want to say it this album
just sounds like a bjork imitation it's
it it just hurts to say because i was
like oh you know i don't think she
sounds that much like bjork to the point
where i would cringe or think okay this
just all right but honestly everything
from the fluttering somewhat glitchy
instrumentation in the background to
the melodic phrasing and the vocals
there are so many songs on this album
that don't even sound like a a myriad of
different places in bjork's ever growing
career a lot of these songs just sound
like they could have been on vespertine
which is my favorite bjork album but
even though it does feel like there is a
clear influence from that album this lp
is way less textured than vespertine and
and way less layered instrumentally and
way less epic as well and honestly
there's not too much about this lp that
i can say
there are a few songs on here that
remind me of a few of the songs on ring
and i don't mind that i think that's
fine i guess i was just
perplexed listening to this album as to
what i kind of see as
a huge step backwards rather than
forwards into
a more interesting or just a more
distinct sound because with the last
full length i think glasser had a pretty
good thing going with this combination
of primal beats and futuristic synthetic
tones and her voice on top of it it was
something that i feel like had potential
and it seems like she in a sense has
sort of scrapped that and while i don't
normally get automatically disappointed
by some artist showcasing an influence
from another artist
this is just one of those cases where
the influence is so deafening
i just don't hear anything else but if
you've given this glass or album a
listen what did you think of it did you
love it hate it why what do you think i
should review next and
that's it
anthony fantano
glasser forever
